David Patrick Neal, 52, was arrested Friday after a hotel guest named Peter Brennan woke at 5am on March 30 to find Neal slobbering all over his phalanges.

Neal was arrested only after the white hot pissed guest filed a formal criminal complaint and law suit against the Nashville-based Hilton. The toe sucker claims he entered Brennan’s room unannounced because he “smelled smoke” and wanted to make sure the guest was safe. 

He did not elaborate on how a sleeping man’s foot ending up in his mouth after that. 

Brennan was previously convicted of voluntary manslaughter for shooting his ex-roommate during an argument; drunk driving; and forgery. 

Neal states he’s had trouble sleeping and feeling calm since the incident, which is FAIR. 

We’re not about kink shaming here at HF, but remember kids: Consent matters.

In today's f*ckery news, Shawn Stone, a 32-year-old man, was arrested by deputies on May 9th for allegedly physically assaulting his girlfriend's 5-year-old son in Volusia County. Sheriff Mike Chitwood disclosed that Stone had used severe punishment methods, including punching, kicking, and using a mop handle to discipline the child for wetting the bed. The boy sustained serious injuries, such as a fractured skull, a lacerated lip, and facial bruises, as well as a mop handle-shaped bruise on his thigh.

The mother reported the abuse after using a camera app on her phone to capture footage of Stone beating her son. She also informed the authorities that Stone had a history of using methamphetamine, although he claimed to have been drug-free for some time.

Stone fled the scene on an all-terrain vehicle (lol) but was later caught and arrested. During questioning, he admitted to slapping the child out of frustration, but he denied the use of a mop handle. Cool, bro.

Stone was charged with aggravated child abuse and is currently being held in Volusia County Jail without bail.

Last week went extremely off the rails for the 48-year-old, identified only as “Lillian” by police, after she took a wrong turn while driving through the Mitta Mitta bush lands. It went from bad to worse when the car got stuck in deep muck in an area of the remote wilderness without cell signal, making it impossible for Lil to let anyone know where she was or call for help. 

A medical condition made it untenable for the stranded driver to walk to 37 MILES to the nearest town, which rescuers said was probably for the best since nighttime temps were around 30 degrees. 

Fortunately for Lillian—a non-drinker—she had a bottle of red in the vehicle which she’d intended to give to her parents as a gift, as well as a handful of lollipops. 

Fashion models have lived, inadvisably, for decades on a diet of wine and juuuuust enough hard candy to keep from passing out, and Australian law enforcement said Lillian’s popping the bottle and sucking on candy helped keep her hydrated and fed just enough to stave off death by dehydration during her 4 night/5 day stay in the middle of fucking nowhere. 

Lillian was eventually spotted on janky roadside by helicopter search teams scouring the area after family suggested she could have gotten lost while en route to a lake she’d planned to visit. 

She was treated and released at a nearby hospital for dehydration and a mild hangover, which is the best possible outcome when you chill in the Death Continent’s outback with nothing but a bottle of cab and some Tootsie pops.

UPDATE: Lori Vallow Daybell was found guilty on Friday for the murders of her two youngest children and a romantic rival, marking the culmination of a three-year investigation. Throughout the trial, bizarre claims emerged, including Vallow Daybell's belief that her son and daughter were zombies and that she was a divine being sent to bring about the Biblical apocalypse.

As the verdict was read, Vallow Daybell remained expressionless, while some individuals in the courtroom gallery wiped away tears.

Prosecutors depicted Vallow Daybell as a power-hungry manipulator who was driven to kill her two youngest children for financial gain. However, the defense argued that she was a protective mother who fell under the influence of a cult leader, her fifth husband, Chad Daybell.

During the final arguments of the seven-week trial, jurors heard both narratives. They deliberated for approximately four hours before adjourning for the evening, resuming their deliberations the following morning. Shortly after noon, they reached a verdict, which was announced to the courtroom.

Vallow Daybell was convicted on charges of conspiring to commit the murders of her 7-year-old son Joshua "JJ" Vallow, 16-year-old daughter Tylee Ryan, and Tammy Daybell. She was also found guilty of grand theft and first-degree murder of the two children, indicating her direct involvement in the crimes.

Chad Daybell, Vallow Daybell's fifth husband, faces the same charges, but his trial is scheduled for several months later.

Throughout the trial, the testimonies presented were both heartbreaking and strange. Colby Ryan, Vallow Daybell's sole surviving child, accused her of murdering his siblings in a recorded jailhouse phone call. Another witness, Melanie Gibb, testified that Vallow Daybell believed certain people in her life had been possessed by evil spirits and turned into "zombies," including JJ and Tylee. According to the testimony, four individuals whom the defendant referred to as "zombies" were later killed or targeted.

A former mortuary worker from Arkansas, Candace Chapman Scott, has entered a plea of not guilty to charges of selling stolen body parts from medical school cadavers. The indictment, which was unsealed in federal court in Little Rock, accuses Scott, 36, of arranging the transactions with a Pennsylvania man she met through a Facebook group focused on "oddities." Scott, who worked at Arkansas Central Mortuary Services, faces 12 counts, including conspiracy to commit mail fraud, mail fraud, conspiracy to commit wire fraud, wire fraud, conspiracy to commit interstate transportation of stolen property, and interstate transportation of stolen property.

According to the indictment, Scott approached the buyer, identified in separate state charges as Jeremy Lee Pauley from Pennsylvania, in October 2021. Over a period of nine months, she allegedly sold him various body parts, including fetuses, brains, hearts, lungs, genitalia, and large pieces of skin, among others. The transactions were facilitated through 16 separate PayPal transfers, totaling $10,975. The indictment cites messages sent by Scott to Pauley, including one inquiring about selling a fully intact, embalmed brain.

Scott is currently in jail, and a hearing to determine if she will be released on bail is scheduled for Tuesday. The buyer, Jeremy Lee Pauley, faces charges in Pennsylvania related to the case. Pennsylvania officials became aware of the scheme after receiving complaints about Pauley. He is charged with abuse of a corpse, receiving stolen property, and dealing in proceeds of unlawful activities.

Prosecutors argue that Scott should remain in custody until trial, emphasizing the gravity of the allegations. The University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences expressed gratitude for the federal charges, highlighting the importance of body donations for medical education and considering those who donate their bodies as "true heroes."

The American “justice” system is a rat’s nest of fuckery, exploitation, and abuse—and @joe_exotic, viral phenomenon and internationally renowned raconteur, is speaking on it from the inside. 

Once focused on self promotion, the Joe Exotic of 2023 has been campaigning heavily for prison reform over the last 24 months…something HF will always get behind. Mr. Exotic was placed in solitary confinement “for his own protection” under suspicious circumstances, denied reliable to private practice lawyers, and held for months in an Atlanta-based federal penitentiary now under investigation for human rights violations, including breaches of the 6th (right to effective legal counsel) and 8th (freedom from cruel and unusual punishment) constitutional amendments. 

So we had Gary set up a call to Butler Federal Medical Center, a prison for inmates with complex health issues, in North Carolina, where Joe Exotic is being evaluated for his second cancer diagnosis in as many years while serving his 20-year sentence. 

The full conversation was a reminder of how deeply unwell our country is, and how people contain multitudes…which is why moral purity tests are an obstacle to real and lasting change. 

Click the link in our bio or stream us free anywhere podcasts live.

Similar to our recent story on Winnie the Pooh, a few years ago, the dickless nature of everyone's favorite lasagna-eating cat created just enough space for a small war to rage surrounding the details of Garfield's gender.

Apparently, there had been ongoing fan speculation regarding whether Garfield is male or female. This debate became so intense that it sparked a fierce 60-hour editing war on Wikipedia, leading to the page being locked down. Surprisingly, the creator of Garfield, Jim Davis, initially sparked the discussion two years prior in an interview titled "20 Things You Might Not Know About Garfield," where he described the character as being universally undefined in terms of gender, race, nationality, age, or any specific attributes.

Initially, Davis's remarks did not cause any controversy. However, when satirist Virgil Texas stumbled upon the article, he modified Garfield's gender on the wiki page from "male" to "none." The internet erupted in response. 

Within an hour, a Wiki editor changed it back to "male," igniting a back-and-forth battle between "male" and "none" for a grueling 3 days days. At one point, the debate extended to Garfield's religion, with his affiliation being altered to Shiite Muslim (lol). Editors presented "evidence" from past comic strips to support their arguments.

After the Wiki page was eventually closed and the controversy devolved into contentious opinion pieces, Garfield's creator, Jim Davis, stepped forward to settle the matter. He confirmed to The Washington Post that Garfield is indeed male and explained that he has a girlfriend named Arlene. This declaration prompted Texas to concede defeat, acknowledging Davis as the ultimate authority on Garfield's identity.

The semantic issue that SEEMS to be at the root of the dispute, is that Davis never suggested that Garfield was not biologically male, as gender specifically refers to social and cultural expressions of identity, which the fat cat appears to be removed from. 

Biological sex ≠ Gender. Gender ≠ Biological sex. 

And that's ok 😂. We can let God sit this one out.

An Ohio fishing tournament organized by the Lake Erie Walleye Trail was shaken by a cheating scandal. 

The winning catches in the tournament were found to be tampered with, filled with lead weights and fish fillets. 🤣

The tournament's director, Jason Fischer, became suspicious of the fishermen who were poised to win the competition when the total weight of their five fish amounted to 34 lbs. This exceeded Fischer's estimate of around 20 lbs., as reported by The Washington Post.

A live stream of the weigh-in, which was shared on the tournament's Facebook page, captured the moment when the two fishermen, Jacob Runyan and Chase Cominsky, presented their fish. The displayed weight was 33.91 lbs., eliciting a sarcastic remark from one attendee who said, "Yeah, right."

In another video, Fischer informed the crowd they had discovered "weights in fish" after slicing one open and removing a lead ball. Following this announcement, numerous participants confronted a member of Runyan and Cominsky's team in anger.

The alleged cheaters would have received $28,760 in prize money from the event. The Lake Erie Walleye Trail tournament involves teams of fishermen competing to catch the heaviest combined weight of five walleyes from Lake Erie. The prize money is derived from the tournament's entry fees, and it was revealed that the accused individuals had won several other competitions organized by Fischer in recent months.

Wildlife officials collected evidence from the tournament's location in Cleveland and are preparing a report for the Cuyahoga County prosecutor's office.
Fischer indicated on Facebook he would release a comprehensive statement during a live stream later that night.

Fischer recalled the moment when the alleged cheating was exposed, stating, "I had to stop myself for a second and say, 'Hey, please, nobody touch these dudes.'" He noted the crowd was furious upon the revelation. Fischer also expressed uncertainty regarding the fate of the tens of thousands of dollars won by the alleged cheaters in earlier tournaments this year. 

Fischer having this job and being named “Fischer” is objectively amazing.

Because why not?

A colossal replica of the moon is envisioned to grace the summit of a skyscraper in Dubai, with an astounding price tag of over £4 billion. Spearheaded by Canadian entrepreneur Michael Henderson, the ambitious plan involves erecting a 274-meter (900-foot) sphere atop a 30-meter (100-foot) edifice in the United Arab Emirates city-state.

Dubai, already renowned for housing architectural marvels like the world's tallest building, aims to offer visitors an extraordinary encounter resembling a journey to the moon, all while remaining firmly planted on Earth. The project, aptly named MOON, anticipates attracting an annual influx of over 2.5 million guests, potentially generating an astonishing £1.5 billion in revenue each year.

Moon World Resorts Inc, co-founded by Henderson, is financing the venture, estimated to cost around £4.28 billion. Henderson exclaims, "Eight billion people know our brand, and we haven't even started yet."

The grand scheme encompasses a resort nestled within the spherical structure, featuring an expansive 4,000-room hotel, a 10,000-capacity arena, a vibrant nightclub, and a wellness center. To offer a truly immersive lunar experience, a 'lunar colony' will enable guests to step foot on the moon's simulated surface, providing a tangible sensation of moonwalking.

The moon replica will be perched atop a pedestal-like building and will radiate a luminous glow at night, imitating a full, half, or crescent moon.

Henderson envisions this endeavor as "the largest and most successful modern-day tourism project in the Middle East and North Africa (MENA) region," propelling Dubai's annual tourism visitations to new heights, owing to its global allure, brand recognition, and an array of unique integrated attractions.

Henderson's project surpasses the MSG Sphere, a $2.3 billion LED-screened dome slated to open in Las Vegas this year. Plans for an additional MSG Sphere in London were abandoned following local opposition concerning light pollution and disruptions. In response to the criticism, Henderson wittily suggests, "It's impossible to please everyone. Perhaps we'll need some dark curtains."

Sometimes you just gotta get sh*t done.

That said, a hospital in western Germany has expressed remorse after it was revealed that one of their surgeons enlisted the help of a cleaner during a toe amputation procedure. The incident took place at Mainz University Hospital in 2020, and fortunately, there were no complications for the patient involved. However, the doctor responsible for the decision has been terminated from their position.

Norbert Pfeiffer, the hospital's CEO, acknowledged that the surgeon made an erroneous judgment by proceeding with the routine procedure despite the absence of a qualified assistant. The patient, who had received a local anesthetic, reportedly became restless during the operation, prompting the doctor to approach a nearby cleaner for assistance. The cleaner was requested to hold the patient's leg and pass surgical instruments, despite lacking any medical training or experience, as reported by the local daily Mainzer Allgemeine Zeitung. The incident was brought to light when a hospital manager discovered the cleaner, holding bloody gauze pads, inside the operating theater.

Pfeiffer expressed deep regret over the situation, stating, "This should never have occurred," according to the German news agency dpa.

Thirteen years had passed since it vanished down a toilet, but fate brought back an anniversary gift.

During March of this year, employees at a water treatment plant in Minnesota were sifting through waste when they stumbled upon Mary Strand's long-lost diamond ring. The ring, which had been given to Strand by her husband, Dave, as a 33rd wedding anniversary present, was discovered amidst the refuse of the plant, 13 years after it had slipped off her finger and into the toilet at their home.

Strand vividly recalled the moment of loss, when the ring swirled and disappeared down the drain. She thought to herself, "He'll never buy me another ring... I felt really bad because it was a gift."

Then, on that fateful day, employees at the Rogers, Minnesota plant, including John Tierney, a mechanical maintenance manager, spotted a glimmer of light amidst the debris.

Recognizing the ring's unique design, Tierney believed that attempting to reunite it with its owner might not be an impossible task. So the Metropolitan Council turned to social media, raising the flag on their discovery, likening it to finding a needle in a haystack.

In a tweet accompanied by an image of a ring amidst hay, they wrote, "Recently, we found a ring at one of our regional wastewater treatment plants. This is a rare occurrence, and we want to return the ring to its owner! Please contact us if you lost a wedding ring down the drain."

The post sparked an influx of calls to the plant, with people hopeful that their lost ring might be the one. Responding to the requests, individuals were asked to submit photos of the ring for identification. Ultimately, two local jewelers scrutinized the pictures and identified one that seemed to be a match. It turned out to be Mary Strand's ring.

The ring, though worn and weathered from its unexpected journey through the plant, was finally back in Strand's possession. Remarkably, the water treatment plant where it was found is situated on a road named Diamond Lake. Strand intends to have the ring reset and ready to wear once again, just in time for her 46th wedding anniversary with her husband.

In these grating times it’s nice to see people fighting for what matters. 🧀 

2023’s new King of Petty, 62-year-old Arnold Wachtel, is suing 123-year-old New York foodstuffers Ottomanelli Bros. Inc. for fraud, negligence, and “deceptive acts” of false advertising. He alleges the company uses a mere four cheeses in its “5 Cheese Ravioli” product. Wachtel was made aware of the inadequate cheese count by….the box’s own ingredient list. 

The lawsuit states “the Ravioli ingredient list reflects only four cheeses: 
1) Ricotta
 2) Pecorino romano 
3) Mozzarella
4) Parmesan”

“How can you claim five cheeses, when there’s only four cheeses?” Jesse Lengel, pasta attorney representing Wachtel, asked The Daily Beast in a statement. 

Worse, Ottomanelli Bro’s apparently shafts consumers a whole ravioli IN ADDITION TO the one unnamed cheese, showing five ravioli on the box photo, but putting only four inside. 

Again, quoting directly from this very serious lactose lawsuit: 

“The phrase ‘5 Cheese Ravioli’ placed above a picture of five ravioli, coupled with the defendant’s intentional omission of a hyphen between ‘5’ and ‘Cheese,’ implies to reasonable consumers that the defendant includes five ravioli in the packages like the ones purchased by Plaintiff.” 

When asked for comment about the alleged deception, third-generation small portion purveyor Frank Ottomanelli said: “People really sue for this stuff? You can’t make this shit up.”

The ravioli-er than thou Plantiff, who currently makes his living helping New Yorkers buy firearm licenses, is requesting $50000 in damages for his suffering, which he says involves “overpayment, disappointment, frustration, trust erosion, and dietary concerns.” Gotta get that cheddar somehow. 

So who’s the bigger asiagohole? King Petty, or Ottomanelli Bros? We feel like it’s a dick move to constipate the court with these fusilli lawsuits, but also a cheese ravioli IS a cheese ravioli…

Do you have what it takes to survive? Veteran Army Intelligence badass and author of “The Instructor” @readtrhendricks sure does, even if we hate it. 🤣

In this month’s “true and truly wild stories” competition, Teams Kimberly & Edward dug up polar opposite pieces of historic survival. Team Kimberly presents the epic saga of Ada Blackjack, a young Inuit woman forced to live off the coast of Siberia alone for MONTHS with no previous hunting or building training. 

Team Edward dredges up the torment of Mauro Prosperi, an ultra-marathon runner  blown by a sandstorm into a 10-day slog through the Sahara without drinking water. 

Special guest Tim Hendricks, whose crazy fun survival thriller novel THE INSTRUCTOR is now available anywhere books are sold, swoops in to assess both tales, pick a winner, and chat bugout bags and PTSD in the process. 

Full episode now live anywhere podcasts live, or ad-free at the link in our bio.

From the anal glands of legendary behavior, according to Van Buren Township Public Safety, a 49-year-old man sustained injuries this morning when he was ejected from a waste collection vehicle and landed in a landfill.

In a Facebook post, the police stated that the vehicle operator had picked up a waste container in Detroit and was in the process of emptying it at the Woodland Meadows Landfill. At that moment, the operator observed the man rising from the ground and departing on foot.

Emergency medical services attended to the man at the scene, and subsequently, he was taken to a nearby hospital for treatment of minor injuries.

There is no word on how he found himself in the garbage truck, or if he plans to make this a regular mode of transportation.

Meirivone Rocha Moraes, 38, married LITERAL rag doll Marcelo in December 2021. But their happy union was severed last month when Moraes got word her inanimate bae was stepping out. “My friend sent me a message one evening saying that he was cheating on me,” she told VERY VERY CURIOUS people watching on the hellsite that is TikTok. 

This apparently led to a one-sided argument, during which Moraes removed her boo’s genitals (a 16cm dildo), then banished him to the couch for the foreseeable future. His dick is being kept in a bedroom drawer until reconciliation is achieved. 

This is not the first time Moraes has caught Marcelo cheating. 

“Last time, I found a bright pink thong on the floor. When I asked whose they were, he didn't answer me,” she told “newspapers,” a term we use soooooooo fucking loosely. 

Moraes and Marcelo were introduced by the bride’s mother, who sewed Marcelo after her daughter complained she was lonely and never had anyone to dance with. “It was love at first sight,” Moraes told NeedToKnow.online.

The pair welcomed a child, Marcelinho, just 6 months later. They apparently live-streamed the birth to roughly 200 viewers, none of whom we want to speak to. They welcomed two more handsewn children, Diego and Carol, over the next 18 months. 

Marcelinho was allegedly kidnapped and held for ransom in February of this year. 

Anyway, this is just a reminder to schedule that follow up with your therapist because holy shit.

THIS is why you ALWAYS establish a safe word! According to German authorities, a 51-year-old man narrowly escaped dying in humiliating fashion after a sexual role-playing encounter took a dangerous turn.

Apparently the man was found fully clothed but securely bound with ropes, head covered a pantyhose, on a deer-hunting platform near the town of Bueckburg on Wednesday evening. His cries were fortunately heard by a cyclist and a hunter in the vicinity.

Police said the man had been restrained by a woman he met online. In what is either the rudest date move, or weirdest kink, ever, the woman abruptly abandoned the bound and hosed man in the woods after receiving …an unexpected phone call? (This detail is sus as hell but whatever.) 

"The 51-year-old informed officers that he had a box cutter with him 'for such situations,' but had underestimated the woman's proficiency in bondage, making it impossible for him to access the knife,” said the official police statement. 

Thankfully, the man remained unharmed. He declined to provide any details regarding the woman's identity, which means it was almost certainly a man…which we support fully, just live your best life out loud dude. 

Authorities have initiated an investigation into the incident, suspecting the “woman”—because women definitely love meeting in deer blinds for dates—of failing to provide assistance and potentially violating the man's freedom.

Juliane Koepcke was 17 and celebrating her high school gradation the day lighting struck her plane over Peru. LANSA, which made Spirit Airlines look like Jay-Z & Beyoncés private jet, was notorious for welding decrepit castaway planes together and covering the scars with new-looking paint. The aircraft carrying Juliane and 80+ other innocent souls began breaking apart like a Lego set in midair.

Which is how Juliane fell 10000 ft. strapped to a commercial airline seat…and landed smack in the middle of the Amazon jungle alone, concussed, but alive. 

What followed was one of the most compelling survival stories in the last 100 years, an 11-day solo trek through the rainforest without so much as a set of shoes to help. Multiple other LANSA passengers survived the initial hellish crash, but only the teenaged girl had the jungle knowledge, perseverance, and good luck to make it back to civilization alive. 

How??

The true story is our most recent Secret Story Time, that immersive mini-show for HF subscribers only, streaming now at the Patreon link in the bio with lush sound design and wild details. 

Scroll, smash, subscribe, and listen today. ⬆️

He went from waving tiki torches to “love is all you need” in about a week’s time, and all it took was a dose of the empathy drug in a proper clinical setting. 

Identified only as Brendan in news articles, the former chud took the federally banned substance—which triggers the release of oxytocin, our body’s endogenous “love drug” which facilitates human bonding—in February 2020 as part of a University of Chicago research project. He self-reported being drawn in by white nationalist propaganda while attending the University of Illinois years prior, going so far as to participate in the now infamous parade of dickheads in Charlottesville back in 2017. 

Brendan’s participation on the Unite the Right fuckery was prominent enough to get him doxxed and fired. (Firing is the correct way to handle White Supremacists if they work for you, PS.) 

Headed up by psychiatrist and behavioral science professor Harriet de Wit, the UC study administered MDMA in a clinical setting to investigate whether the substance could improve antisocial feelings in participants. Following the “trip,” study participants were asked to fill out a survey for the researchers. Brendan wrote on his: “This experience has helped me sort out a debilitating personal issue. Google my name. I now know what I need to do.” 

Researchers initially contacted Brendan to make sure his “need to do” line wasn’t a violent threat, but young man assured them what he needed to do was love everyone and drop the bigot routine. “Love is the most important thing. Nothing matters without love,” he explained. 

Brendan elaborated to author Rachel Nuwer, who’s been writing a book about MDMA research, that: “[MDMA] helped me see things in a different way that no amount of therapy or antiracist literature ever would have done.” 

MDMA, psilocybin, and LSD—despite what The War on Drugs posters told you in the 80s and 90s—have been found to help some brains trapped in entrenched thinking reorganize themselves. They show great promise in the treatment of PTSD, intractable depression, addiction, and isolating social disorders….when used properly. (“Used properly” does NOT mean at an EDM festival.)

Anyway, dose Nazis.

If Musa Hasahya Kasera never slept, never went to the bathroom, and never ate, he’d still only be able to devote 14.11 minutes of quantity one-on-one time per day with each child. 

As of today, he has 568 grandchildren. 

Wrap it up, gentlemen. #happyfathersday #fathersday

A Georgia auto shop owner named Miles Walker thought he, and his coins, were slick. But they ain’t. Walker has been ordered to pay $39,934 in back wages and damages to nine employees, including former employee Andreas Flaten, by federal labor officials. 

The mess began when Flaten complained about not receiving his final paycheck of $915. In retaliation, Walker dumped 91,500 pennies, all coated in oil, in Flaten's driveway + a pay stub containing an offensive message. The U.S. Department of Labor filed a lawsuit against Walker and his company, A OK Walker Autoworks, accusing them of retaliation & failure to properly compensate employees for overtime work.

The lawsuit concluded with a federal judge's consent judgment on June 13. According to the judgment, Flaten will receive $8,690 in back wages…and damages for the greasy insult from his former boss. The investigation by the Department of Labor's Wage and Hour Division revealed that Flaten and eight other workers were also not adequately paid for their overtime hours. Regional Administrator Juan Coria emphasized workers should ALWAYS receive their wages without harassment or intimidation.

In addition to the monetary penalties, the court order requires Walker and his company to adhere to federal minimum wage and overtime regulations. They are also prohibited from making any references to Flaten on the company's website. However, the website of A OK Walker Autoworks still indirectly mentions the "pennies issue" in a post on its testimonials page, suggesting that most reviews between March and July 2021 may be fabricated.

You may have had a bad week, but you didn’t die twice. 

The nightmare scenario went down in Ecuador earlier this month when 76-year-old Bella Montoya, a retired nurse, fell unresponsive after a serious stroke in her nursing home. She was declared legally dead, and a death certificate was issued and passed to her family along with her body. 

What happened next was absolutely bonkers, and wouldn’t be believable if it weren’t on tape. Patreon subscribers get the full story at the link in our bio. They also have our newest SECRET STORY TIME episodes sailing into their inboxes sometime next week, so there’s multiple reason to throw us $3. 

Click the things ⬆️

This week, the police apprehended a mother and her associate under suspicion of mistreating and neglecting two young children and multiple dogs.

As per a news statement issued by the Lexington Police Department, officers conducted a welfare check on Monday, June 26, at a residence on Martin Luther King Jr. Boulevard. During the check, they discovered two girls, aged 9 and 5, who were allegedly subjected to abuse and neglect. The authorities stated that the girls were "confined to a room, malnourished, and subjected to physical abuse."

Upon arriving at the scene, the officers also encountered emaciated and neglected dogs, along with drug paraphernalia.

After further investigation, the police arrested the mother, Julia Owens, aged 31, and her male acquaintance, Josh Hoover, aged 42, who resided in the same house.

Hoover and Owens were subsequently booked into the Davidson County Detention Center on two charges, each of felony child abuse/neglect resulting in serious physical injury, felony cruelty to animals, and possession of drug paraphernalia. They are presently held on a $75,000 bond and are scheduled to appear in court on July 31.

The investigation is currently ongoing, and additional charges may be filed.

According to a press release issued by the Davidson County Sheriff's Office, Owens had previously been arrested in April 2022 on two counts of misdemeanor child abuse. During that incident, detectives responded to her residence on Klopman Mill Road in Denton and discovered conditions that posed a significant risk of physical harm to the minor children.

With domestic terrorists The Proud Boys targeting Pride events and grown men losing their minds over tucking bathing suits, you may sometimes ask yourself “HOW did we get HERE, America?!” One slice of that complicated answer? Pro Wrestling in the 1990s. 

Yep, really. 

Between 25-30% of ALL Americans today identify as pro wrestling fans, and the spectacle streams into BILLIONS of homes globally across 180 countries. More popular than baseball’s World Series and the NCAA playoffs, its mainstream entertainment in a wildly influential way, impacting the lives of people who’ve never even purchased a PPV event. 

Unfortunately, pro wrestling has a looooong and bizarre history of leveraging homophobia to sell tickets, despite being one of THE most obviously homoerotic sports in human history. 

And no pro wrestling character, or giant-painted man’s arc, has spotlighted the hypocrisy of Conservative Queer Hate quite like “Goldust.” 

But despite being used to stoke audiences’ worst fear-based impulses, the man cast as Goldust—Dustin Runnels, aka @dustinrhodestx—is a role model for personal growth and hero of healthy masculinity. He’s a proud parent of a trans child, and outspoken anti-bigotry advocate, thoroughly melting any claims that cishet men who are allies are somehow “betas” or “soybois.” 

The story of Goldust and its lingering relevance in 2023 is as fascinating as it is maddening, even if you think you don’t like pro wrestling or never saw The Bizarre One in gloriously weird action. 

This meticulously researched, fully scored, Pride-themed episode was originally for Patreon subscribers only, but deserves to be heard by the masses. It’s now free and streaming anywhere podcasts live for your enjoyment. 

You can also support episodes like it (and gain immediate access to dozens more) by subscribing at the link in our bio, where we tackle tales as varied as That Time A Bunch of Slavers Handed A Ship Full of Slaves Weapons And Thought Nothing Bad Would Happen; The Bonkers Saga of A Cult Leader Who Got Rich Using Child Labor to Make Denim Jackets; and The Ingenious Tribes Agree Big Foot Was Real.

It’s been “feels like 120” across Louisiana all month; Hurricane Season prep in underway; and we’ve produced 13 feature-length episodes + even more Secret Story Time installments in the last 13 months. Gary the Ghoul has been threatening to join the WGA/SAG strike if we don’t give him a break, and he’s not wrong to do it. Putting together wild, transportive stories for y’all is a passion that drives us, but even the most passionate nerds need a nap. 

Patreon Subscribers will still get their exclusive SST drops this month (July)—and if you’re not yet a subscriber but become one, there’s HOOOOOURS of unhinged immersive true stories waiting to be enjoyed—but there’s no main competition episode coming to the show feed. 

HOWEVER…while our two-person-one-undead-wraith production team IS taking a few weeks off to recharge and batten down the hurricane hatches, they’re also researching  heavily for our SEASON 2 FINALE, landing next month!

In a downtown Tokyo neighborhood, the early morning serenity is interrupted by an unusual sight: a pair of alpacas strolling gracefully through the streets alongside joggers and parents with strollers.

Akane and Satsuki, the two alpacas, are led by their keepers on a leisurely walk, passing by shops, temples, and even pausing to graze on the grass in a small park. They gracefully share the crosswalks with occasional pedestrians before returning to their home at "Alpaca Land," an indoor petting zoo.

After some gentle brushing and grooming, these woolly South American natives are ready for their day, where they get to spend time with visitors eager to interact with them. For a fee of 1,000 yen ($7), guests can enjoy 30 minutes of petting, hugging, and nuzzling their faces into the alpacas' irresistibly soft fleece.

One delighted visitor, Nana Ide, gushed about her experience, sharing how the alpaca's fluffiness covered half of her face when she leaned against its back, creating an incredibly adorable moment.

Shinya Ide, the manager of Alpaca Land (no relation to Nana), believes the key to the alpacas' charm lies in the comfort they bring to people. The simple act of observing them is comforting, but petting them takes it to another level, offering a soothing effect to those who interact with them.

According to Shinya, alpacas are naturally skittish and timid creatures. When approached by unfamiliar people, they may spit or run away, making them challenging to interact with for some. However, Akane and Satsuki are exceptional exceptions. Over their five years at Alpaca Land, they have been trained and have naturally acquired laid-back personalities, making them accustomed to human interaction and enjoyable companions for visitors.

In a tragic and disturbing incident, a well-known YouTube chef named Daniel Sancho Bronchalo has recently faced charges in court for the alleged brutal murder of his boyfriend, Dr. Edwin Arrieta Arteaga, a 44-year-old Colombian plastic surgeon. The incident occurred during their vacation on the beautiful Thai island of Koh Pha Ngan, known for its scenic beaches and vibrant "full moon" parties.

Local authorities revealed that an argument between the couple, related to "sex and money," escalated into a deadly confrontation. The police suspect that the crime may have been premeditated, as there were indications of dubious activities by the suspect before the incident. Daniel Sancho Bronchalo reportedly knew the victim even before they arrived in Thailand.

After attending a full moon party with friends, Mr. Sancho reported his lover missing, but suspicions arose when body parts, including hips and thighs, were discovered by locals at a landfill site on the island. Shockingly, it has been alleged that the accused dismembered Dr. Arteaga's body into 14 pieces and disposed of some in a rubbish dump while using a kayak to discard others at sea in a suitcase, including the victim's head.

Following investigations and DNA tests confirming the identity of the remains, Mr. Sancho was charged with premeditated murder and concealing a corpse to hide the death or cause of death. Reports from other media outlets suggested that the YouTuber had purchased knives, plastic bags, and cleaning supplies from convenience stores on the island.

The accused's family issued a statement seeking respect and understanding during this distressing period of uncertainty. Police have sought the continued detention of Daniel Sancho Bronchalo while further investigations are ongoing.

Peggy Jones, 64, was just trying to mow the damned lawn. A resident of Silsbee, Texas, a sliver of Lone Star state just across the Louisiana border, Jones was pushing her mower around 8pm when a 4.5ft snake literally fell from the sky. The serpent, already in attack mode, immediately wrapped around Jones’ arm, then began BITING HER IN THE FACE repeatedly. The snake’s teeth smashed into Jones’ glasses several times while spraying what appeared to be venom, a stroke of terrifying good luck which likely prevented the victim from being blinded. 

Her good luck ended seconds later, however, when the marauding hawk which dropped the snake swooped down to reclaim its slithering lunchable. The bird attempted to yank the snake back into the sky, but its prey had already wrapped itself snugly around one of Jones’ forearms. 

So the hawk started screaming and slashing Jones with its talons while the snake panicked and flailed. 

After a few moments of bloody, feral chaos, the bird wrenched the snake back and absconded into the sky, leaving Jones traumatized and bleeding in the middle of her yard. 

Mr. Wendell Jones, Peggy’s husband, drove his very shaken wife to the local ER, where she swiftly became “Case of the Day” in the RN break room. Because doctors are the absolute worst, Jones reportedly was asked “Are you sure you’re not on drugs?” instead of simply believing the TALON WOUNDS on her arm weren’t self-inflected. (In the doctors defense, it IS East Texas.) 

Jones has made a full recovery, but told reporters she had briefly thought she was going to die—FAIR—and has been having trouble sleeping since the attack. 

Wendell Jones will be doing the yard work for the foreseeable future.

Little Asa Baker, an Alliance, Ohio, local, was just the latest in a line of smol humans to be radicalized by a nonsensical interaction with local police. The elementary schooler was apparently ratted on by a local festival organizer, butthurt that a child was biting into his “business” by selling $1 cups of lemonade a few blocks from the main entrance of his event.

“The police were really sad that they had to shut me down, but they gave me $20 to try and pay for it,” Baker told Fox News. (The actual cost of the permit was $40.) 

As it turns out, the vast majority of the United States took time at some point to ignore pressing issues, like health care and infrastructure decline, and focus their energy on passing laws which require juveniles to obtain permits before operating a lemonade stand. Nearly 40 states have this kind of legislation on the books, mandating that police act whenever some craven festival organizer calls 911 over $30. 

Louisiana gets basically everything wrong all of the time, but its generally Fascist regime did do the right thing back in 2016, passing Senate Bill 99, aka "The Lemonade Law.” The bill allows children to operate permitless beverage stands…so long as they do not exceed $500 in earnings annually. 

Ain’t no way any state government would ever allow children whose schools they don’t fund to make more than a few Benjamins without getting Government Daddy their cut. 

What a time to be alive!

A 747 cargo plane was barely 30 minutes into its flight to Belgium last week when an adult steed broke out of its stall during turbulence. Once aware of the disregard for Fasten Seatbelt rules, a pilot called New York’s John F. Kennedy International Airport and was like “NOPE, see you in 20 minutes.” 

No one has any idea how the horse broke loose. It was one of 15 breeding and/or show horses being transported to Liege when turbulence rattled the vessel, according to the head of the corporate Animal Shipping authority at JFK. “It’s only the second time in all the years I’ve been doing this that I’ve ever seen that happen,” he said. “And we do thousands of horses a year. A very unfortunate event.”

The jet ultimately U-turned, dumped 20 tons of fuel over the Atlantic “10 miles west of Martha's Vinyard," then requested a veterinarian to be present at JFK when the plane arrived. A vet met the flight on the tarmac in NY, but unfortunately found the distraught passenger badly injured. You already know what happens to injured horses. 

Anytime humans wanna stop doing dangerous shit to animals for absurd profit that would be great.
